.TH "safe_copy_page" 9 "safe_copy_page" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
safe_copy_page \- Copy a page in a safe way.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" safe_copy_page
.BI "(void *dst "  ","
.BI "struct page *s_page "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dst" 12
-- undescribed --
.IP "s_page" 12
-- undescribed --
.SH "DESCRIPTION"

Check if the page we are going to copy is marked as present in the kernel
page tables. This always is the case if CONFIG_DEBUG_PAGEALLOC or
CONFIG_ARCH_HAS_SET_DIRECT_MAP is not set. In that case \fBkernel_page_present\fP
always returns 'true'.
